  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Impact Network  for Street Children Senegal</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Senegal, despite numerous initiatives for collaboration and coordination of programmes for street and working children, many still aren&#x2019;t accessing support. There is duplication of work, a waste of limited available resources, a local lack of communication and real synergy among stakeholders. caused by ideological differences and a tendency to &#x201C;own&#x201D; beneficiaries instead of thinking of the children&#x2019;s best interests. This project will explore ways to strengthen the work of a network set up over ten years ago out of the practical necessity to coordinate street work in Dakar. Activities will include the consultation of beneficiaries through children&#x2019;s and community forums, gathering their first hand experience accessing services. It will critically analyse the activities both of the agencies and networks. Meetings and a national workshop will lead to a strategy for much better collaboration on the ground. The expected outcomes of this project will be that street children will be better protected and have their rights respected. Organisations&#x2019; impact will be enhanced through collaboration, while communities will be empowered to take an active role in the protection of their children.</narrative>
  </description>
